Package: BayesCCal
Title: Bayesian Calibration of Classifiers
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(
	person("Marco", "Puts", email = "mputs@acm.org", role = c("aut", "ctb")),
	person("Martijn", "Tennekes", email = "mtennekes@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Calibration of (binary) classifiers is done using a Bayesian method. First the "proportion positives" is estimated. After that, the probability of an item being positive is estimated.
